You should have a second `if` statement inside your callback function.

```js
const callback = code.split(/const\s+sortSongs\s*=\s*\(\s*\)\s*=>\s*\{/)?.[1]?.split(/\}\s*\)\s*;?\s*\}/)?.[0];
assert.lengthOf(callback?.match(/if\s*\(/g), 2);
