lessons.testCode:
You should call your `printGreeting` function.

```js
assert.match(code, /printGreeting\(\);?/);
```

Your `printGreeting` function call should be below the `printGreeting` function definition.

```js
assert.isBelow(code.indexOf("const printGreeting = () => {"), code.indexOf("printGreeting()"));
```

Your `printGreeting` function call should output `Hello there!` to the console. 

```js
const spy = __helpers.spyOn(console, "log");
